Yeah!

04:21.089 --> 04:22.522
Ooh, ooh, yeah.

04:22.558 --> 04:24.658
We never had this problem
with David Cassidy.

04:24.726 --> 04:25.725
Cassidy was a hack.

04:25.761 --> 04:28.095
Bieber is a [bleep] artist.

04:28.130 --> 04:30.197
[ Panting ]

04:30.232 --> 04:33.400
[ Crack! ]

04:33.435 --> 04:35.736
[ Grunts ]

04:35.771 --> 04:37.537
[ Gun cocks ]

04:49.149 --> 04:50.583
[ Grunts ]

04:52.686 --> 04:59.025
Aah!

04:59.094 --> 05:01.294
You're a hard man to find, Jason.

05:01.330 --> 05:01.828
[ Sighs ]

05:01.864 --> 05:04.364
The list -- look what it makes me do.

05:04.400 --> 05:06.400
Look what it makes me do.

05:06.435 --> 05:09.870
[ Gagging ]

05:09.939 --> 05:11.305
Parcheesi!

05:11.340 --> 05:12.873
Oh, would you look at that?

05:12.909 --> 05:14.675
More blocks.

05:14.711 --> 05:17.012
Yay.

05:17.047 --> 05:17.779
[ Fanfare plays ]

05:17.848 --> 05:20.749
All gifts present and accounted
for, except snake eyes.

05:20.785 --> 05:22.151
He's so hard to buy for.

05:22.186 --> 05:27.156
What's wrong with what we always get him?

05:27.191 --> 05:29.224
I never hear him complain about it.

05:29.260 --> 05:29.691
[ Laughs ]

05:29.727 --> 05:32.227
What are you supposed to get a guy
who won't tell us what he wants?

05:32.296 --> 05:36.131
There is one thing he
wants, and we all know it.

05:38.334 --> 05:40.134
Okay, there's Storm Shadow's house.

05:40.170 --> 05:42.971
We zipline over, bag him, and
get him back to the base for

05:43.040 --> 05:45.975
snake eyes to open on Christmas morning.

05:46.043 --> 05:48.410
All: Yo, Joe!

05:48.446 --> 05:52.315
Take him alive!

05:52.350 --> 05:55.885
All: Yo, Joe!

05:55.920 --> 05:59.989
Oh, baby, I'm sorry.

06:00.058 --> 06:01.157
Ow! Ow!

06:01.192 --> 06:02.959
Ohh, this is not good.

06:02.995 --> 06:04.994
We're not leaving without you, mister.

06:05.029 --> 06:07.597
Yo, Joe!

06:07.632 --> 06:09.599
I got him! I got him!

06:16.908 --> 06:21.612
Merry [bleep] Christmas.

06:21.680 --> 06:23.280
Well, that's true, Mrs. cage.

06:23.316 --> 06:25.349
It only <i>says</i> your card is declined.

06:25.418 --> 06:27.084
I <i>inferred</i> that you were poor.

06:27.119 --> 06:31.354
It's just -- it's been so hard to make
ends meet since my husband passed away.

06:31.390 --> 06:33.690
Cage -- where have I heard that before?

06:33.725 --> 06:34.624
Finish him!

06:34.693 --> 06:35.459
[ Groans ]

06:35.494 --> 06:37.627
Oh, right. That guy I killed.

06:37.663 --> 06:38.528
Wait!

06:38.564 --> 06:41.064
Well, if you're sure I'm not
imposing, I'd love to join you

06:41.100 --> 06:41.999
for Christmas dinner.

06:42.067 --> 06:42.733
Wonderful.

06:42.768 --> 06:44.534
It'll be just like having Johnny back.

06:44.570 --> 06:45.902
You remind me of him, you know?

06:45.971 --> 06:47.204
You have his heart.

06:47.272 --> 06:50.107
Kano rules!

06:50.142 --> 06:52.075
Hyah!

06:52.111 --> 06:54.278
Okay [Grunts] okay.

06:54.347 --> 06:55.746
Hyah!

06:55.815 --> 06:57.481
Oh.

06:57.549 --> 06:58.248
Oh, oh.

06:58.284 --> 06:59.483
Unh-unh.

06:59.551 --> 07:02.353
[ Laughs ]

07:02.388 --> 07:03.354
Listen, Sarah.

07:03.389 --> 07:07.025
This has been a perfect day, but
something I need to confess.

07:07.093 --> 07:07.659
[ Sighs ]

07:07.694 --> 07:08.460
I don't understand.

07:08.528 --> 07:09.728
It's -- it's Johnny's heart.

07:09.763 --> 07:11.096
I was the one who killed him.

07:11.164 --> 07:12.464
Kano, this isn't a heart.

07:12.499 --> 07:13.465
